Johannesburg - A man was killed in an apparent hit-and-run
accident in Benoni, east of Johannesburg, on Tuesday, paramedics said. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said the man, in his 30s,
was found lying on the middle road divider. "Unfortunately the man had already succumbed to his
fatal injuries. The driver of the vehicle was not found on scene," said
Meiring. "Local authorities were on the scene for further
investigations." 